If the sample we tested was 20 people, then I would assume that in another group of 20 people from the same planet, the same number would be thieves. I generally used proportions to figure out how many thieves there were (ie 2 thiefs in sample of 5 corresponds to 8 thiefs in sample of 2020). Where the sample size was low like 1-5, and everyone was thieves or maybe all but one was a thief, it was slightly tough to assume how many out of 20 would be thieves, but I generally applied the same principles of proportion and then subtracted a couple to account for variation because of the small sample size.
